# KTP weekly precache-gap audit — fleet-wide drift detection.
#
# Runs precache_audit.py with --scope all (.res + BSP entdata) on Sunday
# 06:00 ET (after the 03:00 ET fleet restart + .new swap, before Sunday
# matchplay starts ~12:00 ET). Posts a Discord embed to #ktp-updates ONLY
# on actionable severity (CRITICAL/HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW); silent on GREEN or
# INFO-only weeks.
#
# What this catches that ktp-soak-verify doesn't:
#   - ktp-soak-verify checks deployed binaries (md5 drift across .so/.amxx)
#   - This audit checks deployed ASSETS (.spr/.mdl/.wav/.wad/.tga/.bmp)
#     referenced by maps. Different surface, different bug class.
#
# What CAN trigger a post:
#   - CRITICAL: asset referenced by a map missing on 5+ game-server
#     instances (the xrain2.spr 2026-05-01 class — fleet-wide deploy gap)
#   - HIGH:     missing on 1-4 instances (partial-deploy class)
#   - MEDIUM:   present on every game host but missing on FastDL (slow
#     client downloads, no crashes)
#   - LOW:      other drift
#
# What does NOT trigger a post:
#   - INFO: reference host AND ≥80% of fleet missing — stale entdata
#     reference the engine tolerates. Map has shipped this way forever;
#     not a fleet-drift signal. Listed in the saved report.md for
#     operator visibility but not embedded in the Discord post.
#
# Companion to:
#   - /etc/cron.d/ktp-soak-verify-post-restart  (nightly binary drift)
#   - /etc/cron.d/ktp-soak-verify-post-matchday (Mon HLTV F+A health)

SHELL=/bin/bash
PATH=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin
MAILTO=''

# Sun 06:00 ET = 10:00 UTC during EDT, 11:00 UTC during EST.
# Server's TZ=America/New_York handles the conversion; cron evaluates the
# minute/hour fields against local time. Confirm with `timedatectl` on the
# data server (should report America/New_York).
0 6 * * 0   root  /usr/local/bin/ktp-precache-audit --scope all --cron-mode --output /var/log/ktp-precache-audit-$(date +\%Y\%m\%d).md >> /var/log/ktp-precache-audit-cron.log 2>&1
